# App-CloseExp — Flutter Rules

## Architecture
- Keep feature-first + 3-layer structure: `data`, `domain`, `presentation`.
- BLoC only calls UseCases; do not call repository/data source directly from BLoC.
- Use `go_router` for route wiring in `core/router/app_router.dart`.

## Networking & Auth
- Use `dio` + `retrofit` for API integration.
- Keep BE contract aligned with `ApiResponse<T>` semantics.
- Store tokens only in `flutter_secure_storage` (not in shared preferences).

## DI & Codegen
- Use `get_it` + `injectable` pattern.
- Run build_runner after model/retrofit/DI annotation changes.

## Must-Pass Checklist
- [ ] Layer boundaries respected (`presentation -> domain -> data`).
- [ ] DTO/model nullability matches backend contract.
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or API keys.
- [ ] Delivery task/time-slot flows keep canonical slot windows (`19:00-20:30`, `21:00-22:30`) aligned with backend.
- [ ] Validation run: `flutter analyze` and `flutter test`.
- [ ] Run when needed: `flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs`.
